    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="505" ind1="0" ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">1. f. 1v-12v: Umm al-barāhīn fī ʻilm al-kalām [incomplete at end] / Muḥammad ibn Yūsuf al-Sanūsī -- 2. f. 13r-29r: Ṣughrá al-ṣughrá / Muḥammad ibn Yūsuf al-Sanūsī  -- 3. f. 30v-41r: al-Maqṣūd bi-al-niẓām sabk jawāḥiran [thus] min al-kalām / Muḥammad al-Ṣāliḥ al-Awjalī -- 4. f. 42r-86r: Min anwāʻ al-kufr / Abū ʻAbd Allāh Muḥammad ibn ʻUmar -- 5. f. 87r-90v: Fa-inna al-faqīh ʻabd Allāh / Muḥammad al-Ṣāliḥ al-Awjalī  -- 6. f. 91r-123: Salīm / Muḥammad al-Ṣāliḥ al-Awjalī  --7. f. Unnumbered [1r-32]: [Dalīl al-qāʼid li-kashf asrār ṣifāt al-wāḥid (incomplete and out of order)] / Muḥammad al-Ṣāliḥ al-Awjalī -- 8. f. Unnumbered [33-40]: various incomplete leaves</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="510" ind1="4" ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Simsar, Muhammed Ahmed. Oriental manuscripts of the John Frederick Lewis Collection,</subfield>
      <subfield code="c">35.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Foliation: Partially foliated (1-123) followed by 40 unnumbered leaves ; catchwords lower left verso.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Layout: 6-14 long lines; many interlinear glosses.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Script: Written in a maghribi script using an oblique cut pen in black and brown ink; pointed, partially vocalized.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Decoration: Grid of brown and white on opening leaf (f. 1r) covering text that was there first; some rubrications in red.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Binding: Leaves are unbound and have never been bound. They are held between a piece of stiff hide with the hair side inside and a piece of card, wrapped in another piece of hide with patches of spotted hair still attached.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Origin: Copy is undated, though it was completed on a Friday between the morning and the afternoon by Isḥāq [?] (f. 123r); perhaps copied in the 19th century.</subfield>
    </datafield>
